<!--
  Synthetic CCDA fixture for the ChartPDS holdout regression suite.
  Entirely fabricated test data: no real patient, no PHI.

  Two vitals series that rise together monotonically but NOT linearly,
  so rank and linear correlation give different answers:
    - body weight (29463-7) on Jan 15/16/17/18: 380 / 400 / 420 / 440
    - heart rate (8867-4) on Jan 15/16/17/18: 60 / 61 / 63 / 80
  Ranks agree exactly (1,2,3,4 vs 1,2,3,4) -> Spearman rho = 1 exactly.
  Raw deviations (-30,-10,10,30) x (-6,-5,-3,14) -> Pearson
  r = 620 / sqrt(2000*266) ~ 0.85, visibly below 1. A correct
  rank-based spearman_r must report 1.0 here; wiring it to the raw
  Pearson value is the regression this fixture exists to catch.
-->
